        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A–6 Recall that if f (x) is a polynomial with integer coeff - cients, then m − n divides f (m) − f (n) for any integers m and n. In particular, if we put bn = an+1 − an, then bn divides bn+1 for all n. On the other hand, we are given that ao = am = 0, which implies that a1 = am+1 and so b0 = bm. If b0 = 0, then a0 = a1 = . . = am and we are done. Otherwise, |b0| = |b1| = |b2| = · . ·, so bn = ±b0 for all n.",
